# Architecture: {{ display_name }}

## Overview

{{ display_name }} is a Django REST Framework backend organized around a conventional Django project plus explicit domain apps. The blueprint assumes Django is a first-class choice because the ORM, admin ecosystem, and DRF tooling are part of the intended implementation path.

## High-Level Structure

```text
Clients
  |
DRF routers / viewsets
  |
serializers + permissions
  |
services / use-case modules
  |
Django ORM models
  |
{{ database | title }}
```

## Repository Layout

- `config/` for settings, URLs, and environment wiring
- `apps/api/` for REST resources and API composition
- `apps/users/` for identity and access concerns
- `apps/common/` for shared building blocks

## Responsibilities

### Viewsets and API Views

- HTTP orchestration only
- select serializer class, permission class, and service entrypoint
- never become the home of complex workflow branching

### Serializers

- request validation
- output shaping
- light data transformation

Serializers should not become service substitutes.

### Services / Use Cases

- workflow orchestration
- cross-model business rules
- integration coordination

### Models

- persistence structure
- low-level invariants
- query behavior where Django conventions make that natural

